                  </hi>. I live in Lloyd-square, Clerkenwell, and am an engineer. On 6th April, I was in front of a shop in Gray's-inn-lane—I felt some one against my pocket—I went on a step or two, and then felt some<lb></lb>thing again—I turned round and saw the prisoner passing from me—I missed my handkerchief—the prisoner ran, and I called, "Stop thief!"—he dropped this handkerchief and was stopped by a gentleman—I went up, took him by the collar, and gave him in charge—he said he had picked the handker<lb></lb>chief up—it is mine (<hi rend="italic">looking at it</hi>).</p>
